column1: Note: The standard error of the estimate, when multiplied by 1.645 and added to or substracted from
the estimate, represents the 90-percent confidence interval around the estimate.

Source: Counts for the 2010 Census are from 2010 Census Summary File 1;  preferred estimates are from 2010 Census Summary File 1 using the methodology outlined in this paper;  2010 American Community Survey.
